This paper focuses on evaluating machine learning models for analyzing software programs, which falls under the intersection of several computer science subfields. The most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper discusses recent advances in neural program embeddings. The next likely category is cs.SE (Software Engineering), as the paper discusses the challenges of analyzing large software and proposes a benchmarking framework for evaluating models. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely, as the paper discusses the use of machine learning to model program semantics. cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category, as the paper discusses program transformations and refactoring. Finally, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a possible category, as the paper discusses the use of natural language processing techniques to analyze program code.
